/**
 * HeroAnimations.css
 * Extracted from faceiqlabs.com HAR file
 *
 * IMPORTANT FINDING: The original site does NOT use a gradient shimmer animation
 * on the "Harmony" text. Instead, it uses:
 * 1. A simple blue color (text-blue-400 / #60a5fa)
 * 2. A rotating word animation with fade/slide transitions
 */

/* =============================================
   ROTATING TEXT ANIMATION
   The h1 cycles through words: proportions, symmetry,
   harmony, ratios, measurements, balance
   ============================================= */

.rotating-text {
  display: inline-block;
  color: #60a5fa; /* Tailwind text-blue-400 */
  min-width: 280px;
  transition: all 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
}

.rotating-text.fade-out {
  opacity: 0;
  transform: translateY(10px);
}

.rotating-text.fade-in {
  opacity: 1;
  transform: translateY(0);
}

/* =============================================
   FADE-IN ANIMATION (Intersection Observer)
   Applied to sections as they scroll into view
   ============================================= */

.fade-in {
  opacity: 0;
  transform: translateY(20px);
  transition: opacity 0.6s ease, transform 0.6s ease;
}

.fade-in.visible {
  opacity: 1;
  transform: translateY(0);
}

/* =============================================
   HERO SECTION CONTAINER
   ============================================= */

.hero-section {
  position: relative;
  overflow: hidden;
  min-height: max(100vh, 720px);
  height: 100vh;
  background: #0d1117;
}

/* =============================================
   3D HEAD CONTAINER
   The head3d element hosts the Three.js canvas
   ============================================= */

.head3d-container {
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  min-height: max(100vh, 720px);
  z-index: 0;
  pointer-events: none;
  transform: translate3d(0, 0, 0);
  will-change: transform;
  contain: layout style paint;
}

.head3d-container > canvas {
  position: absolute !important;
  inset: 0 !important;
  width: 100% !important;
  height: 100% !important;
  z-index: 0;
  display: block;
  transform: translate3d(0, 0, 0);
  will-change: transform;
  backface-visibility: hidden;
}

/* =============================================
   VIGNETTE OVERLAY
   Creates the gradient fade effect around the 3D head
   ============================================= */

.vignette-overlay {
  position: absolute !important;
  top: 0 !important;
  bottom: 0 !important;
  left: 0 !important;
  width: 100% !important;
  pointer-events: none !important;
  z-index: 2 !important;
  opacity: 0.8 !important;
  transform: translate3d(0, 0, 0);
  will-change: opacity;
  background:
    linear-gradient(to right, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.65) 0%, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5) 20%, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35) 35%, transparent 55%),
    linear-gradient(to top, #0d1117 0%, transparent 40%),
    linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2) 0%, transparent 30%),
    radial-gradient(ellipse at 55% 50%, transparent 35%, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.18) 60%, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35) 82%, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5) 100%);
}

/* =============================================
   RESPONSIVE STYLES
   ============================================= */

/* Small mobile (< 400px) */
@media (max-width: 400px) {
  .hero-section {
    height: 100vh !important;
    min-height: max(100vh, 720px) !important;
  }

  .head3d-container {
    width: 100vw !important;
    height: 100vh !important;
    min-height: max(100vh, 720px) !important;
    left: -1.5rem !important;
  }

  .vignette-overlay {
    opacity: 0.6 !important;
  }

  .hero-text {
    position: absolute !important;
    top: 2rem !important;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem !important;
    padding-right: 1.25rem !important;
    z-index: 30;
  }

  .hero-text h1 {
    font-size: 1.75rem !important;
    line-height: 1.2 !important;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem !important;
  }

  .hero-text p {
    font-size: 0.875rem !important;
    margin-bottom: 1rem !important;
  }
}

/* Larger mobile (401px - 799px) */
@media (min-width: 401px) and (max-width: 799px) {
  .hero-section {
    height: 100vh !important;
    min-height: max(100vh, 720px) !important;
  }

  .head3d-container {
    width: 100vw !important;
    height: 100vh !important;
    min-height: max(100vh, 720px) !important;
    left: -1.5rem !important;
  }

  .vignette-overlay {
    opacity: 0.6 !important;
  }

  .hero-text {
    position: absolute !important;
    top: 2rem !important;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    padding-left: 0 !important;
    padding-right: 0 !important;
    z-index: 30;
  }

  .hero-text h1 {
    font-size: 2.25rem !important;
    line-height: 1.2 !important;
    margin-bottom: 1rem !important;
  }

  .hero-text p {
    font-size: 1rem !important;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem !important;
  }
}

/* Tablet (800px - 1023px) */
@media (min-width: 800px) and (max-width: 1023px) {
  .hero-text {
    width: 50% !important;
    position: relative !important;
    padding-top: 2rem !important;
  }

  .hero-text h1 {
    font-size: 2rem !important;
    line-height: 1.2 !important;
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem !important;
  }

  .hero-text p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem !important;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem !important;
  }
}

content.text:
Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me analyze the root causes of the animation issues.

## Bug Summary

The animations in the looksmaxx-app appear to be correctly implemented but there are several issues that could cause them to appear static or not work properly.

## Root Cause Analysis

After tracing through the code, I have identified the following root causes:

---

### ROOT CAUSE 1: HeadScene Animation Loop Starts Before Scene is Initialized

**File:** `/Users/imorgado/LOOKSMAXX/looksmaxx-app/src/components/HeadScene.tsx:590`

**The bug occurs because:** The animation loop (`requestAnimationFrame(animate)`) is started in the `useEffect` hook at line 590 BEFORE the scene is fully initialized. The `initScene()` function is called, but it is NOT awaited - the model loading happens asynchronously via `GLTFLoader.load()`. This means:

1. Animation starts immediately
2. `sceneRef.current.headModel` is `null` during the initial frames
3. The animation loop at line 487-489 checks `if (headModel)` - which is `null`, so the head doesn't animate
4. The model loads asynchronously and sets `sceneRef.current.headModel` later

**However**, the animation SHOULD continue once the model is loaded because the animation loop keeps running. The real issue is elsewhere.

---

### ROOT CAUSE 2: useCallback Dependencies Cause Stale Closures

**File:** `/Users/imorgado/LOOKSMAXX/looksmaxx-app/src/components/HeadScene.tsx:446-550`

**The bug occurs because:** The `animate` function is wrapped in `useCallback` with an empty dependency array `[]` at line 550. This creates a closure that captures the initial values of `sceneRef` and other variables. While `sceneRef` is a ref and should work, the pattern is problematic.

More critically, the `initScene` function (line 94-443) is also wrapped in `useCallback` with empty dependencies, and it creates the animation reference. But since `animate` is defined with `useCallback([], [])`, it captures a stale closure that may not see updated `sceneRef.current` values properly in some React strict mode scenarios.

---

### ROOT CAUSE 3: FloatingScoreCard Score Animation Only Runs Once

**File:** `/Users/imorgado/LOOKSMAXX/looksmaxx-app/src/app/page.tsx:205-226`

**The bug occurs because:** The score animation in `FloatingScoreCard` uses `useEffect` with an empty dependency array `[]`. This means:

1. Animation runs ONCE when component mounts
2. After 2 seconds (duration 2000ms), it reaches target score 4.27 and stops
3. Score becomes static permanently

The user expects continuous animation or dynamic score changes, but the animation is one-shot by design.

```typescript
// Lines 205-226 - One-shot animation
useEffect(() => {
  const targetScore = 4.27;
  const duration = 2000;  // Animation runs for 2 seconds then stops forever
  // ... animation logic
}, []); // Empty deps = only runs once
```

---

### ROOT CAUSE 4: RotatingText and FloatingAdviceCard DO Animate (No Bug Here)

**Files:** 
- `/Users/imorgado/LOOKSMAXX/looksmaxx-app/src/app/page.tsx:99-128` (RotatingText)
- `/Users/imorgado/LOOKSMAXX/looksmaxx-app/src/app/page.tsx:133-195` (FloatingAdviceCard)

These components have proper interval-based animations that should work:
- `setInterval` every 2500ms for RotatingText
- `setInterval` every 3000ms for FloatingAdviceCard
- `requestAnimationFrame` for floating motion

If these appear static, the issue is likely that the components are not visible (hidden behind overlays or z-index issues) rather than the animation logic itself.

---

### ROOT CAUSE 5: HeroBackground Component is Unused

**File:** `/Users/imorgado/LOOKSMAXX/looksmaxx-app/src/components/HeroBackground.tsx`

**The bug occurs because:** The `HeroBackground` component exists but is NOT imported or used in `page.tsx`. The page uses its own inline implementations:
- `RotatingText` is defined inline in page.tsx (lines 99-128)
- `FloatingAdviceCard` is defined inline in page.tsx
- `HeadScene` is dynamically imported

The `HeroBackground.tsx` file contains a `RotatingText` export that is never used, creating confusion about which implementation is active.

---

### ROOT CAUSE 6: Framer Motion Animations May Not Trigger Due to SSR/Hydration

**File:** `/Users/imorgado/LOOKSMAXX/looksmaxx-app/src/app/page.tsx` (multiple locations)

**The bug occurs because:** The page uses `motion` components with `initial="hidden"` and `animate="visible"`. These should work, but:

1. The `whileInView` animations (used in most sections) require scrolling to trigger
2. If the user doesn't scroll, sections below the fold remain in `hidden` state
3. The hero section animations use `animate="visible"` which should trigger immediately

The framer-motion version `12.23.26` is very recent and may have breaking changes from older versions the code was designed for.

---

## Trace Path

1. **Animations appear static**
   - HeadScene: Model loads asynchronously, animation loop starts before model exists
   - FloatingScoreCard: One-shot animation completes after 2 seconds and stops
   - Other sections: `whileInView` animations wait for scroll trigger

2. **Score values should animate but don't**
   - `FloatingScoreCard.displayScore` animates from 0 to 4.27 over 2 seconds
   - After 2 seconds, score is static at 4.27 forever
   - No continuous animation loop for score changes

3. **Components not appearing dynamically**
   - `motion.div` with `initial="hidden"` starts invisible
   - `animate="visible"` should trigger but may fail on hydration
   - `whileInView` requires scroll to trigger

---

## Recommended Fixes

### Fix 1: FloatingScoreCard - Add Continuous Score Animation

```typescript
// In FloatingScoreCard, replace the one-shot animation with a continuous loop
useEffect(() => {
  const scores = [4.27, 7.85, 6.42, 8.12, 5.91];
  let currentIndex = 0;

  const cycleScore = () => {
    const targetScore = scores[currentIndex];
    const startScore = displayScore;
    const duration = 1500;
    const startTime = Date.now();

    const animate = () => {
      const elapsed = Date.now() - startTime;
      const progress = Math.min(elapsed / duration, 1);
      const eased = 1 - Math.pow(1 - progress, 3);
      setDisplayScore(startScore + (targetScore - startScore) * eased);

      if (progress < 1) {
        requestAnimationFrame(animate);
      }
    };

    requestAnimationFrame(animate);
    currentIndex = (currentIndex + 1) % scores.length;
  };

  cycleScore();
  const interval = setInterval(cycleScore, 4000);
  return () => clearInterval(interval);
}, []);
```

### Fix 2: HeadScene - Ensure Animation Starts After Scene Ready

```typescript
// Move animation start into model load callback or use a flag
const [sceneReady, setSceneReady] = useState(false);

// In GLTFLoader.load success callback:
setSceneReady(true);

// Start animation only when ready
useEffect(() => {
  if (sceneReady) {
    animationRef.current = requestAnimationFrame(animate);
  }
  return () => {
    if (animationRef.current) {
      cancelAnimationFrame(animationRef.current);
    }
  };
}, [sceneReady, animate]);
```

### Fix 3: Add Hydration Safety for Framer Motion

```typescript
// Add mounted state to prevent hydration mismatch
const [isMounted, setIsMounted] = useState(false);

useEffect(() => {
  setIsMounted(true);
}, []);

// In JSX:
{isMounted && (
  <motion.div
    variants={fadeIn}
    initial="hidden"
    animate="visible"
    // ...
  />
)}
```

---

## Regression Test

A test that would have caught this:

```typescript
describe('FloatingScoreCard', () => {
  it('should continue animating score after initial animation completes', async () => {
    render(<FloatingScoreCard />);

    // Wait for initial animation to complete
    await waitFor(() => {
      expect(screen.getByText(/4\.27/)).toBeInTheDocument();
    }, { timeout: 3000 });

    // Wait additional time and verify score changes
    const initialScore = screen.getByText(/\d+\.\d+/).textContent;
    await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 5000));
    const laterScore = screen.getByText(/\d+\.\d+/).textContent;

    // Score should have changed if animation is continuous
    expect(laterScore).not.toBe(initialScore);
  });
});
```

---

## Prevention

1. **Document animation behavior** - Specify whether animations are one-shot or continuous
2. **Use animation state machine** - Track animation lifecycle (idle, running, paused, complete)
3. **Add loading states** - Don't start dependent animations until prerequisites are ready
4. **Test on hydration** - Verify animations work after SSR hydration in Next.js
